The application simulates basic equipment rental service.
There are functions like adding users, adding equipment, seeing available equipment, rent equipment and return it(main functions)
The ui is done in console.
I orginized code in folders: "Model" contains basic data classes, like Equipment
"Services"  contains main buisness logic, like renting, returning and limiting
"Database" has Singleton(storage for users, equipment and etc.)
and Program.cs for console output.
Structured code is easy to understand and helps avoiding mixing responsibilities.

Business rules included:
Students can have max 2 active rentals
Employees can have max 5
Equipment marked as Unavailable cannot be rented
Late returns generate a penalty (5 per day)
Overdue rentals are detected automatically
All rules are kept in one place (RentalService) so they are easy to change.

Cohesion - each class in the project has one clear job, and all of its fields and methods relate to that job.
In Equipment classes only store info about equipment, User stores only user data and etc.

Coupling - in Program.cs it only talks to the IRentalService interface, not to the database or models directly

